[8] Italy: Measles and Rubella Integrated Surveillance System
Date: Wed 3 May 2017
Source: ISS [machine translated, edited. - Mod.SH]
http://www.epicentro.iss.it/problemi/morbillo/Infografica2017.asp


In order to monitor and describe the measles epidemic in our country in January 2017, the Ministry of Health and the ISS have started producing a weekly bulletin that provides an overview of the distribution of cases reported to the Measles and Rubella Integrated Surveillance System, by region, age range and vaccination status.

The following data cover the period from 1 Jan 2017 to 30 Apr 2017:
- 1920 cases reported since the beginning of the year;
- 18 of the 21 regions have reported cases, but 92 per cent of cases came from 7: Piedmont, Lazio, Lombardy, Tuscany, Abruzzo, Veneto and Sicily;
- 88 per cent of cases were unvaccinated and 8 had received one single dose of vaccine;
- the median age of cases was 27 years; most cases (73 per cent) were reported in people aged 15 years or older; 120 cases were less than one year of age;
- 176 cases occurred in health care workers;
- 29 cases were reported in the last week (epidemiological week 17: 24-30 Apr 2017).
The data are tabulated at http://www.epicentro.iss.it/problemi/morbillo/bollettino/Measles_WeeklyReport_N6eng.pdf.

