"Measles is a very contagious infectious disease, transmitted by the air contaminated by the coughing or sneezing of an infected person," said the Indian Ocean Health Agency. The agency recommends that people under the age of 50 and those who plan to travel should check with health professionals that they are well protected against the disease.

